might lose your media darling halo

2069
02:28:35,540 --> 02:28:38,460
if the media start sniffing
around our dirty laundry.

2070
02:28:38,540 --> 02:28:42,330
Sir, I never had anything to do with
that and I resent the implication...

2071
02:28:42,420 --> 02:28:46,880
Resent it all you want, Henry,
but you're in with the rest of us.

2072
02:28:46,960 --> 02:28:51,340
Cambodia. Ellsberg.
The wiretaps you put in.

2073
02:28:51,430 --> 02:28:54,640
The president wants you to know
you can't just click your heels

2074
02:28:54,720 --> 02:28:58,020
and head back to Harvard Yard.
It's your ass too, Henry,

2075
02:28:58,100 --> 02:29:01,560
and it's in the wind
twisting with everyone else's.

2076
02:29:11,530 --> 02:29:14,320
- Sir.
- Yeah?

2077
02:29:14,410 --> 02:29:19,580
There are times when
even the president can go too far.

2078
02:29:23,460 --> 02:29:26,670
You played it perfectly, sir.
That cocksucker'll think twice

2079
02:29:26,750 --> 02:29:29,130
- before he leaks again.
- Yeah.

2080
02:29:29,210 --> 02:29:32,840
He'll be looking in his toilet bowl
every time he pulls the chain.

2081
02:29:34,800 --> 02:29:36,260
Hunt wants more money.

2082
02:29:36,350 --> 02:29:38,720
- Another 122,000.
- Fuck.

2083
02:29:38,810 --> 02:29:42,350
If he doesn't get it right away,
he's going to blow us out of the water.

2084
02:29:42,440 --> 02:29:45,360
He means it. Since his wife died
in the plane crash, he's over the edge.

2085
02:29:45,440 --> 02:29:47,020
Pay him. Pay him what he wants.

2086
02:29:47,110 --> 02:29:51,490
We gotta turn the faucet off on Hunt and
these Cubans. They're out of control.

2087
02:29:51,570 --> 02:29:53,780
John, you might want to...

2088
02:29:53,860 --> 02:29:55,950
It's gotta be Helms. He's behind this.

2089
02:29:56,030 --> 02:29:58,490
- I think we can leverage Helms.
- How?

2090
02:29:58,580 --> 02:30:02,870
When I met with him,
he kind of tipped his hand.

2091
02:30:02,960 --> 02:30:05,210
This affair,
the president wants you to know,

2092
02:30:05,290 --> 02:30:07,960
is related to the Bay of Pigs.
And if it comes out...

2093
02:30:08,040 --> 02:30:10,380
This has nothing to do
with the Bay of Pigs!

2094
02:30:11,800 --> 02:30:14,050
I have no concern
about the Bay of Pigs!

2095
02:30:14,130 --> 02:30:16,390
<i>I couldn't believe it.</i>

2096
02:30:16,470 --> 02:30:19,850
This is what the president
told me to relay to you, Dick.

2097
02:30:19,930 --> 02:30:22,390
I had to remind him
who he was talking to.

2098
02:30:22,480 --> 02:30:26,190
So I was wondering? What's such
dynamite in this Bay of Pigs thing?

2099
02:30:26,270 --> 02:30:27,980
Sir.

2100
02:30:31,400 --> 02:30:35,410
Though it was clearly effective, because
all of a sudden it was no problem

2101
02:30:35,490 --> 02:30:38,660
for Helms to go to the FBI
and try to put a lid on Watergate.

2102
02:30:39,530 --> 02:30:43,120
- What about the documents promised?
- He'll give us the documents.

2103
02:30:43,200 --> 02:30:46,750
But I think if we offer him
an ambassadorship,

2104
02:30:46,830 --> 02:30:50,040
the ambassadorship to Iran,
we can get rid of him. He'll go...

2105
02:30:50,130 --> 02:30:54,760
- No, I promised Iran to Townsend.
- Townsend in Belgium. It's available.

2106
02:30:54,840 --> 02:30:59,430
He gave us 300 grand. Belgium's
not worth more than 100, 150.

2107
02:30:59,510 --> 02:31:01,180
What about England?

2108
02:31:01,260 --> 02:31:04,100
Forget it.
Annenberg's paid three times that much.

2109
02:31:04,180 --> 02:31:07,350
Helms wants Iran,
or there might be a problem.

2110
02:31:07,440 --> 02:31:10,230
All his old buddies are over there
making a fortune...

2111
02:31:10,320 --> 02:31:11,780
When does this end, Bob?

2112
02:31:11,860 --> 02:31:13,360
- Executive clemency.
- What?

2113
02:31:13,440 --> 02:31:17,570
Hunt and the Cubans have nothing to lose
now. Pardon them all.

2114
02:31:17,660 --> 02:31:20,780
Nobody investigates a crime
for which criminals have been pardoned.

2115
02:31:20,870 --> 02:31:22,910
- Yeah, I like that.
- But it'll never do.

2116
02:31:22,990 --> 02:31:26,370
Pardoning them means we're guilty.
Press, the people'll go nuts.

2117
02:31:26,460 --> 02:31:29,290
Am I supposed to sit here
and watch them coming closer,

2118
02:31:29,380 --> 02:31:31,040
eating their way to the center?

2119
02:31:31,130 --> 02:31:33,250
Lyndon bugged, so did Kennedy.

2120
02:31:33,340 --> 02:31:37,970
F.D.R. cut a deal with Lucky Luciano.
Christ, even Eisenhower had a mistress.

2121
02:31:38,050 --> 02:31:41,470
What's so special about me? Huh?

2122
02:31:41,550 --> 02:31:46,020
What about Lyndon? He could make
a couple calls to the... Hell, and...

2123
02:31:46,100 --> 02:31:48,600
...shut this whole damn thing down.

2124
02:31:48,690 --> 02:31:50,310
- Anyone talk to him?
- I have.

2125
02:31:50,400 --> 02:31:52,650
- What'd he say?
- No dice, he hit the roof.

2126
02:31:52,730 --> 02:31:54,110
Why?

2127
02:31:54,190 --> 02:31:57,650
He said if you go out with a story
about how he bugged your plane,

2128
02:31:57,740 --> 02:31:59,610
he's gonna reveal...

2129
02:32:08,040 --> 02:32:09,620
He's gonna reveal...

2130
02:32:10,580 --> 02:32:12,840
- ...Vietnamese peace talks...
- All right.

2131
02:32:12,920 --> 02:32:14,840
All right! Stop!

2132
02:32:14,920 --> 02:32:16,590
What's the matter with you?

2133
02:32:18,050 --> 02:32:22,680
I know. I just know
we've made too many enemies.

2134
02:32:23,430 --> 02:32:27,350
There's another thing. Bob and I have to
testify before the urban committee.

2135
02:32:27,430 --> 02:32:30,650
No, you're not.
You're gonna claim executive privilege.

2136
02:32:30,730 --> 02:32:33,020
You're gonna stonewall it
all the way.

2137
02:32:33,110 --> 02:32:35,440
Plead the 5th Amendment.
I don't give a shit.

2138
02:32:35,530 --> 02:32:38,190
They can't force
the president's people to testify.

2139
02:32:38,280 --> 02:32:40,820
Executive privilege
looks like we're covering.

2140
02:32:40,910 --> 02:32:43,320
We are covering up
for God's sake.

2141
02:32:43,410 --> 02:32:45,450
Some petty, stupid shit.

2142
02:32:46,540 --> 02:32:50,460
There are things I can say what
other people said, and they'd be lies.

2143
02:32:50,540 --> 02:32:53,790
When I say them,
nobody believes me anyway.

2144
02:32:55,550 --> 02:32:58,300
Then, we're going to
have to give them Mitchell.

2145
02:33:00,220 --> 02:33:02,510
Mitchell's family.

2146
02:33:02,590 --> 02:33:05,680
Either it goes to Mitchell,
or it comes here.

2147
02:33:07,020 --> 02:33:08,810
John's right, boss.

2148
02:33:09,980 --> 02:33:13,730
It's not personal.
It's just the way the game is played.

2149
02:33:13,810 --> 02:33:16,150
Sometimes you gotta punt.

2150
02:33:21,820 --> 02:33:23,410
Jesus.

2151
02:33:23,490 --> 02:33:26,580
I'm so goddamn worn-out with this.

2152
02:33:35,710 --> 02:33:37,300
Who's gonna tell Mitchell?

2153
02:33:37,380 --> 02:33:39,050
- You do it.
- Why me?

2154
02:33:39,710 --> 02:33:43,300
'Cause he hates you. It's worse
when you get it from someone you trust.

2155
02:33:43,380 --> 02:33:45,510
Hey. He's wrong, you know.

2156
02:33:47,060 --> 02:33:49,640
About Kennedy and L.B.J. and Truman.

2157
02:33:49,720 --> 02:33:50,770
How so?

2158
02:33:50,850 --> 02:33:54,310
Well, I mean, sure, they did stuff, Bob,
but nothing like this.

2159
02:33:54,400 --> 02:33:59,610
I mean, forget about the break-in,
the, the enemies list, the... You know?

2160
02:33:59,690 --> 02:34:03,200
You got the attempted firebombing
of the Brookings Institution.

2161
02:34:03,280 --> 02:34:06,620
Planting McGovern stuff
on the guy that shot Wallace?

2162
02:34:06,700 --> 02:34:08,740
Trying to slip L.S.D. to Jack Anderson?

2163
02:34:08,830 --> 02:34:11,330
Old man plays politics
harder than anybody else.

2164
02:34:11,410 --> 02:34:13,620
You think this is about politics?

2165
02:34:13,710 --> 02:34:17,420
Do you think L.B.J. would have
ever asked Hunt to forge a cable

2166
02:34:17,500 --> 02:34:21,300
implicating Kennedy in the assassination
of the president of Vietnam?

2167
02:34:21,380 --> 02:34:23,590
How long have you known Bob,
20 years?

2168
02:34:23,680 --> 02:34:27,140
This is the Roosevelt Room,
named after our 26th president

2169
02:34:27,220 --> 02:34:29,430
20 years, you ever shake hands with him?

2170
02:34:29,510 --> 02:34:31,850
Ever have a real conversation with him?

2171
02:34:34,310 --> 02:34:37,650
No, this...
This is about Richard Nixon.

2172
02:34:37,730 --> 02:34:40,980
You got people dying because
he didn't make varsity football.

2173
02:34:41,070 --> 02:34:43,650
You got the Constitution hanging by
a thread

2174
02:34:43,740 --> 02:34:47,070
because he went to Whittier,
not to Yale.

2175
02:34:47,740 --> 02:34:49,990
And what is this Bay of Pigs thing?

2176
02:34:50,080 --> 02:34:52,250
Goes white every time you mention it.

2177
02:34:54,120 --> 02:34:57,790
- It's a code or something.
- Well, shit, even I figured that out.

2178
02:34:59,210 --> 02:35:01,090
I think he means...

2179
02:35:03,010 --> 02:35:05,720
- The Kennedy assassination...
- Yeah?

2180
02:35:05,800 --> 02:35:10,180
They went after Castro and in some
crazy way it got turned back on Kennedy.

2181
02:35:10,260 --> 02:35:14,390
I don't think the old man knows what
happened. But he's afraid to find out.

2182
02:35:14,480 --> 02:35:17,690
He's shitting peach pits every time
he thinks about it.

2183
02:35:17,770 --> 02:35:20,480
Created a Frankenstein
with those damn Cubans.

2184
02:35:20,570 --> 02:35:23,400
Eight words back in '72:

2185
02:35:23,480 --> 02:35:29,160
"I covered up." "I was wrong."
"I'm sorry."

2186
02:35:29,240 --> 02:35:31,950
And the American public
would've forgiven him.

2187
02:35:32,040 --> 02:35:35,160
But we never opened our mouths, John.

2188
02:35:36,120 --> 02:35:38,040
We failed him.

2189
02:35:38,120 --> 02:35:42,210
Dick Nixon saying "I'm sorry"?
That'll be the day.

2190
02:35:42,300 --> 02:35:44,880
His whole suit of armor would fall off.

2191
02:35:44,960 --> 02:35:49,180
- So, you tell Mitchell.
- Yeah.

2192
02:35:49,260 --> 02:35:53,260
And John, you do know
that we're next, don't you?

2193
02:36:08,490 --> 02:36:10,620
You're early, John.

2194
02:36:12,950 --> 02:36:16,660
If you'd been that stealthy at the
Watergate, we wouldn't be in this mess.

2195
02:36:18,660 --> 02:36:22,210
- I was sorry to hear about your wife.
- Yes.

2196
02:36:23,880 --> 02:36:25,550
Take out the money.

2197
02:36:25,630 --> 02:36:28,760
The president would like to know
if that was the last payment.

2198
02:36:28,840 --> 02:36:31,510
- I'll bet he would.
- Is it?

2199
02:36:32,970 --> 02:36:35,930
In Richard Nixon's long history
of underhanded dealings

2200
02:36:36,020 --> 02:36:39,810
he's never had better value for his
money. If I were to open my mouth,

2201
02:36:39,890 --> 02:36:42,440
all the dominoes would fall.

2202
02:36:43,860 --> 02:36:45,940
Can I ask you a question?

2203
02:36:46,030 --> 02:36:47,940
How the hell do you have the temerity

2204
02:36:48,030 --> 02:36:50,910
to blackmail the president
of the United States?

2205
02:36:50,990 --> 02:36:55,200
That's not the question, John.
The question is, why is he paying?

2206
02:36:55,280 --> 02:36:59,120
- To protect his people.
- I'm one of his people.

2207
02:36:59,210 --> 02:37:02,580
The Cubans are his people.
And we're going to jail for him.

2208
02:37:02,670 --> 02:37:06,550
Howard, you will serve no more
than two years, then he'll pardon you.

2209
02:37:06,630 --> 02:37:09,760
Maybe. Maybe not.

2210
02:37:10,880 --> 02:37:13,850
But you don't leave your men
on the beach, John.

2211
02:37:13,930 --> 02:37:16,640
You don't make them beg for their money
like thieves.

2212
02:37:16,720 --> 02:37:20,060
You don't dump men with families
who've served their country.

2213
02:37:20,140 --> 02:37:23,150
He didn't know.
This thing has gotten out of hand.

2214
02:37:23,230 --> 02:37:27,070
You think a man as controlled as Richard
Nixon would've allowed a break-in

2215
02:37:27,150 --> 02:37:30,570
at the Democratic National Headquarters
without knowing it?

2216
02:37:30,650 --> 02:37:35,280
You think Mitchell or Haldeman wouldn't
have run it by him at least once?

2217
02:37:35,370 --> 02:37:37,950
The president's men did nothing,

2218
02:37:38,040 --> 02:37:41,750
nothing without
Richard Nixon's permission.

2219
02:37:45,380 --> 02:37:47,550
John, sooner or later...

2220
02:37:47,630 --> 02:37:52,180
Sooner, I think, you're going to learn
the lesson that's been learned

2221
02:37:52,260 --> 02:37:55,760
by everyone who's ever
gotten close to Richard Nixon.

2222
02:37:55,850 --> 02:38:00,930
That he's the darkness
reaching out for the darkness.

2223
02:38:02,520 --> 02:38:06,310
And eventually it's either you or him.

2224
02:38:08,860 --> 02:38:11,570
Your grave's already been dug, John.

2225
02:38:25,080 --> 02:38:28,380
<i>F.B.I. director-designate
L. Patrick Gray</i>

2226
02:38:28,460 --> 02:38:31,170
<i>shocked the Senate
by revealing that John Dean</i>

2227
02:38:31,260 --> 02:38:34,680
<i>has been secretly receiving
F.B.I. reports on Watergate.</i>

2228
02:38:34,760 --> 02:38:37,010
Crown, this is Echo Six.
How are you, sir?

2229
02:38:37,090 --> 02:38:40,060
<i>Gray also said that Dean lied
when he claimed Howard Hunt</i>

2230
02:38:40,140 --> 02:38:42,390
<i>did not
have an office in the White House.</i>

2231
02:38:42,480 --> 02:38:44,690
- How is he?
- He's in a bad mood.

2232
02:38:44,770 --> 02:38:47,020
He's running late. Have a seat.

2233
02:38:51,030 --> 02:38:53,530
This is the sort of thing
Mafia people can do.

2234
02:38:53,610 --> 02:38:56,990
Washing money, things like that.
We don't know about these things

2235
02:38:57,070 --> 02:38:59,990
- because we're not criminals.
- How much you need?

2236
02:39:01,160 --> 02:39:06,370
I would say these people will cost a
million dollars over the next two years.

2237
02:39:06,460 --> 02:39:09,250
We could get that.

2238
02:39:09,340 --> 02:39:13,510
Get a million dollars in cash.
I know where it could be gotten.

2239
02:39:16,380 --> 02:39:19,100
I'm still not confident
we can ride through this.

2240
02:39:19,180 --> 02:39:22,810
Some people are gonna have to go
to jail. Hunt's not the only problem.

2241
02:39:22,890 --> 02:39:27,600
Haldeman let me use the $350,000 cash
fund in his safe to make the payments.

2242
02:39:27,690 --> 02:39:31,440
Ehrlichman had a role, a big role,
in the Ellsberg break-in.

2243
02:39:31,520 --> 02:39:33,570
Oh, I don't know about that.

2244
02:39:33,650 --> 02:39:37,820
And... And I'm...

2245
02:39:37,910 --> 02:39:41,660
I think it's time we begin to think
in terms of cutting our losses.

2246
02:39:45,370 --> 02:39:49,460
Are you... You're saying
cut our losses, John, and all the rest.

2247
02:39:49,540 --> 02:39:53,670
And, you know, suppose the thing blows
and they indict Bob and the others?

2248
02:39:53,750 --> 02:39:56,970
Jesus, you'd never recover
from that, John. I mean...

2249
02:39:57,050 --> 02:40:01,220
No, it's better to fight it out instead
and not let people testify.

2250
02:40:01,300 --> 02:40:05,890
Sir, I, I still don't think
we can contain this anymore.

2251
02:40:06,810 --> 02:40:10,560
There's a cancer on the presidency,
and it's growing with every day...

2252
02:40:10,650 --> 02:40:12,360
Jesus, you know, every...

2253
02:40:12,440 --> 02:40:16,360
Everything's a crisis among the upper
intellectual types, the softheads.

2254
02:40:16,440 --> 02:40:19,490
The average people don't think
it's much of a crisis.

2255
02:40:19,570 --> 02:40:22,950
For Christ's sake, this is not Vietnam.
No one's dying here.

2256
02:40:23,030 --> 02:40:25,160
I mean, isn't it ridiculous?

2257
02:40:25,240 --> 02:40:28,250
- I agree. It's ridiculous but...
- It's goddamn crazy!

2258
02:40:28,330 --> 02:40:30,120
Goldwater was right when he said

2259
02:40:30,210 --> 02:40:34,210
"For Christ's sakes, everybody bugs
everybody else." We know that.

2260
02:40:35,340 --> 02:40:39,720
It's the cover-up, John,
not the deed, that's really bad here.

2261
02:40:41,590 --> 02:40:46,020
If only Mitchell could step up
and take the brunt of it, you know.

2262
02:40:46,100 --> 02:40:50,270
Give 'em the hors d'oeuvre. Maybe they
won't come back for the main course.

2263
02:40:52,100 --> 02:40:54,860
You know, that's the tragedy
in all this. Uh...

2264
02:40:54,940 --> 02:40:58,780
Mitchell's gonna get it anyway,
so it's time he assumed responsibility.

2265
02:40:58,860 --> 02:41:00,780
You're not paying attention.

2266
02:41:00,860 --> 02:41:04,280
He won't. He's told Ehrlichman he won't.

2267
02:41:04,370 --> 02:41:07,870
You tell my good friend Dick
I got suckered into this thing

2268
02:41:07,950 --> 02:41:11,790
by not paying attention
to what these bastards were doing.

2269
02:41:11,870 --> 02:41:15,210
I don't have a guilty conscience,
and he shouldn't either.

2270
02:41:16,800 --> 02:41:18,050
Yeah.

2271
02:41:22,470 --> 02:41:23,760
Well, he's right.

2272
02:41:24,720 --> 02:41:28,310
Maybe it is time to, uh,
go the hang-out route, John.

2273
02:41:28,390 --> 02:41:31,730
A full and thorough investigation.

2274
02:41:31,810 --> 02:41:36,190
We've cooperated with the F.B.I.
We'll cooperate with the Senate.

2275
02:41:36,270 --> 02:41:39,240
- What have we got to hide?
- No, we've nothing to hide.

2276
02:41:39,320 --> 02:41:41,740
No. Nothing to hide.

2277
02:41:41,820 --> 02:41:42,910
You know, the only...

2278
02:41:42,990 --> 02:41:46,490
The only fault in the plan is
they're not gonna believe the truth.

2279
02:41:46,580 --> 02:41:50,200
- That's the incredible thing.
- I agree. It's... it's tricky.

2280
02:41:51,210 --> 02:41:53,710
Everything seems to lead back here.

2281
02:41:53,790 --> 02:41:56,540
- People would never understand.
- No.

2282
02:41:56,630 --> 02:42:00,010
John, I want you to get away
from this madhouse.

2283
02:42:00,090 --> 02:42:01,880
I want these reporters.

2284
02:42:01,970 --> 02:42:06,760
I want you to go up to Camp David
for the weekend and write up a report.

2285
02:42:06,850 --> 02:42:10,140
Put everything you know
about Watergate in there and say,

2286
02:42:10,220 --> 02:42:13,020
"Mr. President, here it all is." OK?

2287
02:42:13,100 --> 02:42:15,980
You want me to put it all in writing
over my signature?

2288
02:42:17,190 --> 02:42:21,820
Well, uh... nobody knows more
about this thing than you do, John.

2289
02:42:21,900 --> 02:42:24,990
You know, the details.
That stuff I don't know. But.

2290
02:42:29,290 --> 02:42:33,910
Sir, I'm not going to
be the scapegoat for this.

