2513
02:59:50,620 --> 02:59:53,160
Can the president afford
to ignore a subpoena?

2514
02:59:53,240 --> 02:59:57,170
Who the hell does Cox think he is? I've
never made a dime from public office.

2515
02:59:57,250 --> 03:00:00,340
I'm honest. My dad died broke. Jesus.

2516
03:00:00,420 --> 03:00:04,760
That son of a bitch Cox, he went
to the same law school as Jack Kennedy.

2517
03:00:04,840 --> 03:00:07,510
The last gasp of the establishment.

2518
03:00:07,590 --> 03:00:10,550
Yeah, they got the hell
kicked out of 'em in the election

2519
03:00:10,640 --> 03:00:12,970
so now they gotta squeal
about Watergate

2520
03:00:13,060 --> 03:00:15,980
'cause we were the first
real threat to them in years.

2521
03:00:16,060 --> 03:00:21,560
My God, we would've changed it so they
couldn't have changed it back in years.

2522
03:00:21,650 --> 03:00:22,860
Yeah.

2523
03:00:24,940 --> 03:00:27,650
- If only the, uh...
- Mr. President.

2524
03:00:27,740 --> 03:00:30,450
- Sir, Congress is...
- No, over here, sir.

2525
03:00:30,530 --> 03:00:33,700
Sir, Congress is considering
four articles of impeachment.

2526
03:00:33,790 --> 03:00:37,250
- Yeah. For what?
- They're very serious charges, sir.

2527
03:00:37,330 --> 03:00:39,000
- First, abuse of power.
- Yep.

2528
03:00:39,080 --> 03:00:41,460
- Second, obstruction of justice.
- What else?

2529
03:00:41,540 --> 03:00:44,460
Third, the failure
to cooperate with Congress.

2530
03:00:44,550 --> 03:00:48,220
- And last, bombing Cambodia, sir.
- Can't impeach me for Cambodia.

2531
03:00:48,300 --> 03:00:50,390
The president can bomb anybody he likes.

2532
03:00:50,470 --> 03:00:53,350
- That's true.
- We'll win that, but the other three...

2533
03:00:53,430 --> 03:00:55,600
- Fred, they sell tickets.
- It's Ron, sir.

2534
03:00:55,680 --> 03:00:58,560
They sell tickets to an impeachment
like a damn circus.

2535
03:00:58,640 --> 03:01:01,480
OK, so they impeach me.
Well, fuck 'em!

2536
03:01:02,900 --> 03:01:05,690
Yeah, well,
it's just a matter of mathematics.

2537
03:01:05,780 --> 03:01:08,150
How many votes we have in the Senate?

2538
03:01:08,240 --> 03:01:10,490
- About a dozen.
- A dozen?

2539
03:01:10,570 --> 03:01:13,240
Jeez, I got half of 'em elected.

2540
03:01:13,320 --> 03:01:18,250
OK, so I got the South
and Goldwater and his boys.

2541
03:01:19,580 --> 03:01:21,540
I'll take my chances in the Senate.

2542
03:01:21,620 --> 03:01:23,380
- Yes, we should.
- This damn leg.

2543
03:01:23,460 --> 03:01:25,960
Well, then, sir, we'll, uh...

2544
03:01:26,050 --> 03:01:29,380
...have to deal with the possibility
of removal from office,

2545
03:01:29,470 --> 03:01:33,260
loss of pension and possibly...
possibly even prison.

2546
03:01:33,340 --> 03:01:37,020
Yeah, well, plenty of people
did their best writing in prison.

2547
03:01:37,100 --> 03:01:39,930
- Gandhi, Lenin.
- That's right.

2548
03:01:40,020 --> 03:01:42,980
What I know about this country,
I could rip it apart.

2549
03:01:43,060 --> 03:01:46,860
If they want a public humiliation,
that's what they'll get.

2550
03:01:46,940 --> 03:01:50,740
- Yes, they will.
- I'll never resign this office. Never.

2551
03:01:50,820 --> 03:01:54,530
- Where the fuck am I? What's in there?
- The P.O.W.s and their families.

2552
03:01:54,620 --> 03:01:57,540
- I'm supposed to be...
- Compassionate, grateful...

2553
03:01:57,620 --> 03:01:58,750
- Proud.
- Sir?

2554
03:01:58,830 --> 03:02:01,120
- Proud. Of them.
- Oh, yes, of course.

2555
03:02:01,210 --> 03:02:03,630
- Fire him.
- Who?

2556
03:02:03,710 --> 03:02:08,460
- Cox. Archibald Cox. Fire him!
- He works for the attorney general.

2557
03:02:08,550 --> 03:02:11,550
- Only Richardson can fire him.
- May I echo my concern, sir?

2558
03:02:11,630 --> 03:02:16,140
- Then tell Richardson to fire him!
- Well, Richardson won't do that, sir.

2559
03:02:16,220 --> 03:02:18,890
- He'll resign.
- The hell he will. Then fire him too.

2560
03:02:18,970 --> 03:02:22,140
If you have to go down to the janitor
at the justice department

2561
03:02:22,230 --> 03:02:23,810
fire that son of a bitch.

2562
03:02:23,900 --> 03:02:27,440
Mr. President, may I
just say something, sir?

2563
03:02:29,070 --> 03:02:31,570
I think that you should
welcome this subpoena.

2564
03:02:31,650 --> 03:02:33,570
- Why?
- Well, sir,

2565
03:02:33,660 --> 03:02:37,080
the tapes can only prove
that Dean was a liar. Right?

2566
03:02:37,160 --> 03:02:39,580
That's right, sir.

2567
03:02:42,660 --> 03:02:45,000
Well, there's more.

2568
03:02:45,080 --> 03:02:47,170
There's more than just me.

2569
03:02:47,250 --> 03:02:49,840
You can't break, my boy.

2570
03:02:49,920 --> 03:02:52,260
Even though it's ended.

2571
03:02:52,340 --> 03:02:55,800
You can't admit,
even to yourself, when it's gone.

2572
03:02:57,010 --> 03:02:59,930
Do you think those P.O.W.s
in there did?

2573
03:03:00,770 --> 03:03:03,350
Now, there's some people,
and we both know them, Al

2574
03:03:03,430 --> 03:03:06,020
think you can go stand
in the middle of a bull ring

2575
03:03:06,100 --> 03:03:07,980
and cry "mea culpa, mea culpa,"

2576
03:03:08,060 --> 03:03:12,280
while the crowd is hissing
and booing and spitting on you.

2577
03:03:13,110 --> 03:03:16,950
Well, a man doesn't cry. I don't cry.

2578
03:03:17,700 --> 03:03:20,950
You don't cry. You fight.

2579
03:03:24,790 --> 03:03:26,040
OK.

2580
03:03:26,120 --> 03:03:30,380
Ladies and gentlemen,
the president of the United States!

2581
03:03:35,380 --> 03:03:39,470
<i>Good evening. We interrupt this program
for a special report from NBC news.</i>

2582
03:03:39,550 --> 03:03:41,220
<i>The country is in the midst</i>

2583
03:03:41,310 --> 03:03:45,230
<i>of what may be the most serious
constitutional crisis in its history.</i>

2584
03:03:45,310 --> 03:03:49,150
<i>President Nixon has fired special
prosecutor Archibald Cox.</i>

2585
03:03:49,230 --> 03:03:51,650
<i>Attorney General Elliot Richardson
has quit</i>

2586
03:03:51,730 --> 03:03:55,530
<i>and his deputy William Ruckelshaus
was fired when he refused to fire Cox.</i>

2587
03:03:55,610 --> 03:03:58,530
<i>Attorney General Robert Bork
executed Nixon's orders,</i>

2588
03:03:58,610 --> 03:04:01,870
<i>- fired the prosecutor.
- ...to head off impeachment proceedings</i>

2589
03:04:01,950 --> 03:04:05,870
<i>the president has agreed to release
transcripts of 46 taped conversations.</i>

2590
03:04:05,960 --> 03:04:09,250
<i>In a simple ceremony, Gerald
Ford was sworn in as vice president.</i>

2591
03:04:09,330 --> 03:04:13,920
<i>Citing wrongdoing, a judge has dismissed
all charges against Daniel Ellsberg.</i>

2592
03:04:14,010 --> 03:04:17,680
<i>A grand jury has indicted former
Nixon aides Haldeman, Ehrlichman...</i>

2593
03:04:17,760 --> 03:04:21,260
You're a lawyer, for God's sake.
How can you let this shit go through?

2594
03:04:21,350 --> 03:04:24,470
- Look. This. Nixon can't say that.
- Well, you did say it, sir.

2595
03:04:24,560 --> 03:04:26,770
Never! I never
said that about Jews.

2596
03:04:26,850 --> 03:04:30,270
- Makes me sound like an anti-Semite.
- We can check the tapes again.

2597
03:04:30,350 --> 03:04:34,940
No need. I know what I said.
Have you lost your mind? Look, Al!

2598
03:04:35,030 --> 03:04:38,820
Nixon can't say this!
"Niggers. Niggers." It can't say that!

2599
03:04:38,910 --> 03:04:41,450
- We could delete it.
- We're doing the best we can.

2600
03:04:41,530 --> 03:04:44,580
- It's not good enough!
- Would you have us black it out, sir?

2601
03:04:44,660 --> 03:04:48,790
- We could write "expletive deleted."
- Cut all these "goddamns"

2602
03:04:48,870 --> 03:04:51,960
and "Jesus Christs" out. Jesus.

2603
03:04:52,040 --> 03:04:56,340
Mr. President. Don't you see that all
these deletion marks in the transcripts

2604
03:04:56,420 --> 03:04:59,880
make it look as though you...
you do nothing but swear?

2605
03:05:04,010 --> 03:05:06,270
It soils my mother's memory.

2606
03:05:06,350 --> 03:05:10,310
You think I want the whole goddamn
world to see my mother like this?

2607
03:05:10,390 --> 03:05:12,730
Raising a dirty-mouth?

2608
03:05:12,810 --> 03:05:17,150
We could start again, sir, but we
don't really have the staff to do that.

2609
03:05:17,240 --> 03:05:20,490
Then start over! Just start over!

2610
03:05:20,570 --> 03:05:23,660
The world will see only what I show 'em!

2611
03:05:23,740 --> 03:05:26,450
From page one, Al. Page one, Ron!

2612
03:05:26,540 --> 03:05:28,960
Ron, get in there and do something.

2613
03:05:29,040 --> 03:05:31,210
All this stuff.

2614
03:05:37,590 --> 03:05:40,300
Five seconds, Mr. President.

2615
03:05:40,380 --> 03:05:44,760
And four, three, two...

2616
03:05:49,850 --> 03:05:52,900
Good evening, my fellow Americans.

2617
03:05:52,980 --> 03:05:54,940
Tonight I'm taking an action

2618
03:05:55,020 --> 03:05:57,860
unprecedented in the history
of this office.

2619
03:05:57,940 --> 03:06:01,530
<i>I had no knowledge of the cover-up
till John Dean told me about it</i>

2620
03:06:01,610 --> 03:06:04,490
<i>- on March 21st, a year ago.
- I think I'm going to throw up.</i>

2621
03:06:04,570 --> 03:06:06,830
<i>...no payment to Hunt
or anyone else be made.</i>

2622
03:06:06,910 --> 03:06:11,370
<i>- He's lost touch with reality.
- I've made my mistakes,</i>

2623
03:06:11,460 --> 03:06:14,830
<i>but in all my years of public life,
I have never profited.</i>

2624
03:06:14,920 --> 03:06:18,250
Can you imagine
what this man would have been

2625
03:06:18,340 --> 03:06:21,220
<i>- had he ever been loved?
- I've earned every penny.</i>

2626
03:06:21,300 --> 03:06:25,010
<i>In all of my years of public life
I have never obstructed justice.</i>

2627
03:06:25,090 --> 03:06:28,560
It's a tragedy
because he had greatness in his grasp.

2628
03:06:28,640 --> 03:06:32,230
<i>- I welcome this examination.
- But had the defects of his qualities.</i>

2629
03:06:32,310 --> 03:06:35,060
<i>- I made $250,000...
- They'll crucify him.</i>

2630
03:06:35,150 --> 03:06:37,270
Does anybody
really care anymore?

2631
03:06:37,360 --> 03:06:40,030
<i>...which many of you
were good enough to purchase.</i>

2632
03:06:41,570 --> 03:06:44,910
And what happens after?

2633
03:06:44,990 --> 03:06:46,740
<i>...every year.</i>

2634
03:06:48,160 --> 03:06:51,870
<i>When l, in 1968 decided to become
a candidate for the president,</i>

2635
03:06:51,950 --> 03:06:56,580
<i>I decided to clean the decks
and to put everything in real estate.</i>

2636
03:06:56,670 --> 03:07:00,420
<i>So, that's where the money came from.
That's all I own.</i>

2637
03:07:00,500 --> 03:07:03,510
<i>That's what we have,
and that's what we owe.</i>

2638
03:07:03,590 --> 03:07:06,840
<i>Because people have got to know
whether or not their president...</i>

2639
03:07:06,930 --> 03:07:08,930
<i>...their president is a crook.</i>

2640
03:07:09,010 --> 03:07:12,850
<i>Well, l am not a crook.
I've earned everything I have</i>

2641
03:07:12,930 --> 03:07:14,560
<i>...doesn't have a mink coat.</i>

2642
03:07:14,640 --> 03:07:17,520
<i>She does have a respectable
Republican cloth coat.</i>

2643
03:07:17,610 --> 03:07:20,940
<i>And I always tell her
she'd look good in anything.</i>

2644
03:07:21,030 --> 03:07:26,860
<i>There has never been any feathering
of nests. Not in this administration.</i>

2645
03:07:27,620 --> 03:07:29,330
<i>Now, let me just say this.</i>

2646
03:07:29,410 --> 03:07:32,450
<i>And I want to say this
to the television audience...</i>

2647
03:07:32,540 --> 03:07:35,790
<i>Supreme Court ruled today
eight to nothing that Nixon's claims</i>

2648
03:07:35,870 --> 03:07:38,710
<i>of executive privilege
cannot be used in criminal cases</i>

2649
03:07:38,790 --> 03:07:42,300
<i>- and must turn over subpoenaed tapes.
- The House Judiciary Committee</i>

2650
03:07:42,380 --> 03:07:44,300
<i>has voted 27 to 11</i>

2651
03:07:44,380 --> 03:07:47,050
<i>to recommend impeachment
to the House.</i>

2652
03:07:47,130 --> 03:07:49,800
<i>The deliberations
now go to the House floor.</i>

2653
03:07:49,890 --> 03:07:53,640
<i>In its report, the committee offers
evidence Nixon obstructed justice</i>

2654
03:07:53,720 --> 03:07:57,770
<i>on at least 36 occasions, that he
encouraged his aides to commit perjury</i>

2655
03:07:57,850 --> 03:08:00,980
<i>and that Nixon abused
the powers of his office.</i>

2656
03:08:01,070 --> 03:08:03,650
<i>In a separate report,
the Senate Select committee</i>

2657
03:08:03,730 --> 03:08:07,570
<i>details the misuse of the l.R.S.,
the F.B.l., the C.l.A.</i>

2658
03:08:07,660 --> 03:08:09,660
<i>and the justice department.</i>

2659
03:08:09,740 --> 03:08:12,490
<i>It denounces the plumbers
and it raises the question</i>

2660
03:08:12,580 --> 03:08:17,370
<i>of whether the United States
had a valid election in 1972.</i>

2661
03:08:31,010 --> 03:08:32,430
Come in.

2662
03:08:44,440 --> 03:08:49,740
Victory at Sea, Al. Henry.
The Pacific Theatre.

2663
03:08:49,820 --> 03:08:53,910
Christ, you can almost hear the waves
breaking over the decks.

2664
03:08:59,500 --> 03:09:02,330
I'm afraid we have another problem,
Mr. President.

2665
03:09:03,170 --> 03:09:04,960
Excuse me, gentlemen.

2666
03:09:09,590 --> 03:09:12,140
June 23rd, '72, sir.

2667
03:09:14,810 --> 03:09:19,270
Your instructions to Haldeman
regarding the C.I.A. and the F.B.I.

2668
03:09:20,520 --> 03:09:22,060
So?

2669
03:09:22,150 --> 03:09:26,900
Your lawyers feel that
it's the smoking gun.

2670
03:09:26,980 --> 03:09:30,240
Totally out of context.
I was protecting the national security.

2671
03:09:30,320 --> 03:09:32,910
Sir, the deadline is today.

2672
03:09:36,080 --> 03:09:38,040
Can we get around this, Al?

2673
03:09:39,370 --> 03:09:43,920
It's the Supreme Court, sir.
You don't get around it.

2674
03:09:47,760 --> 03:09:49,880
If, uh...

2675
03:09:49,970 --> 03:09:54,260
If you resign, you can keep your tapes
as a private citizen.

2676
03:09:54,350 --> 03:09:56,970
You could fight them for years.

2677
03:09:59,850 --> 03:10:01,770
What if I stay?

2678
03:10:04,690 --> 03:10:07,270
You have the army.

2679
03:10:07,360 --> 03:10:08,940
The army?

2680
03:10:10,900 --> 03:10:12,360
Lincoln used it.

2681
03:10:19,200 --> 03:10:20,700
That was civil war.

2682
03:10:22,000 --> 03:10:23,370
How do you see this?

2683
03:10:27,130 --> 03:10:28,460
Oh, God.

2684
03:10:28,550 --> 03:10:31,590
We can't survive this, sir.

2685
03:10:34,550 --> 03:10:39,220
They also have you instructing Dean
to make the pay off to Hunt.

2686
03:10:39,310 --> 03:10:43,390
There's nothing in that statement
the president can't explain.

2687
03:10:43,480 --> 03:10:48,980
Sir, you talked about opening up
the whole Bay of Pigs thing again.

2688
03:10:49,070 --> 03:10:52,150
- That's right.
- Three days before, the June 20th tape.

2689
03:10:52,240 --> 03:10:55,950
- The one with the 18-minute gap.
- I don't know anything about that.

2690
03:10:56,030 --> 03:10:59,160
You mentioned
the Bay of Pigs several times.

2691
03:10:59,240 --> 03:11:03,290
Sooner or later, they're going to
want to know what that means.

2692
03:11:03,370 --> 03:11:06,290
They're going to want to
know what's on that gap.

2693
03:11:06,380 --> 03:11:09,630
It's gone. No one will
ever find out what's on it.

2694
03:11:12,380 --> 03:11:16,510
They might if there was
another recording.

2695
03:11:18,850 --> 03:11:20,760
We both know it's possible.

2696
03:11:25,520 --> 03:11:29,190
I know for a fact
that it's possible.

2697
03:11:32,280 --> 03:11:33,740
I've spoken to Ford.

2698
03:11:33,820 --> 03:11:38,660
There's a very strong chance
that he'll pardon you.

2699
03:11:38,740 --> 03:11:42,580
I don't need a goddamned deal,
for God's sake. I...

2700
03:11:42,660 --> 03:11:47,670
This is something that
you will have to do, Mr. President.

2701
03:11:49,710 --> 03:11:54,130
I thought you'd rather do it now.

2702
03:11:58,640 --> 03:12:00,640
I'll wait outside.

2703
03:12:05,890 --> 03:12:07,650
Sir.

2704
03:12:08,810 --> 03:12:12,230
May I say, sir, that if you stay now,

2705
03:12:12,320 --> 03:12:16,570
it will paralyze the nation
and its foreign policy.

2706
03:12:20,160 --> 03:12:23,490
You always had a great
sense of timing, Henry.

2707
03:12:23,580 --> 03:12:27,370
When to give and when to take.

2708
03:12:30,460 --> 03:12:34,210
How do you think Mao
and Brezhnev will react?

2709
03:12:34,300 --> 03:12:37,590
Do you think they'll
remember us, Henry,

2710
03:12:37,680 --> 03:12:40,390
after all the great things
you and I did together,

2711
03:12:40,470 --> 03:12:45,310
as some kind of...
of crooks?

2712
03:12:45,390 --> 03:12:50,100
They will understand.
To be undone by a third-rate burglary

2713
03:12:50,190 --> 03:12:53,190
is a fate of biblical proportions.

2714
03:12:55,400 --> 03:12:59,280
History will treat you far more
kindly than your contemporaries.

2715
03:12:59,360 --> 03:13:01,120
Yeah.

2716
03:13:01,200 --> 03:13:04,990
Depends who writes the history books.

2717
03:13:05,080 --> 03:13:08,540
I'm not a quitter, never have been.

2718
03:13:08,620 --> 03:13:11,540
But I'm not stupid either.

2719
03:13:11,630 --> 03:13:15,130
A trial would kill me.
That's what they want.

2720
03:13:15,210 --> 03:13:19,220
They won't get it. Fuck 'em.

2721
03:13:41,530 --> 03:13:45,620
If they harass you, I too will resign,
and I will tell the world why.

2722
03:13:45,700 --> 03:13:49,540
Don't be stupid.
The world needs you, Henry.

2723
03:13:51,080 --> 03:13:53,540
You always saw the big picture.

2724
03:13:57,090 --> 03:14:00,010
You were my equal in many ways.

2725
03:14:09,350 --> 03:14:12,310
You're the only friend I got, Henry.

2726
03:14:14,940 --> 03:14:17,270
Do you ever pray?

2727
03:14:18,440 --> 03:14:23,780
You know, believe in a supreme being?

2728
03:14:25,490 --> 03:14:29,700
Not really.
You mean on my knees?

2729
03:14:33,710 --> 03:14:37,290
My mother used to pray a lot.

2730
03:14:37,380 --> 03:14:42,300
It's been a long time
since I really prayed.

2731
03:14:48,060 --> 03:14:50,890
Let's pray, Henry.

2732
03:14:50,970 --> 03:14:55,480
Let's pray a little.
Just you and me.

2733
03:15:03,610 --> 03:15:06,410
I hope this doesn't embarrass you,
Henry.

2734
03:15:06,490 --> 03:15:09,330
No. Not at all, no.

2735
03:15:09,410 --> 03:15:13,500
This is not going to leak, is it?

2736
03:15:15,960 --> 03:15:19,000
Don't be too proud, Henry.

2737
03:15:19,090 --> 03:15:23,760
Never be too proud
to go on your knees before God.

2738
03:15:35,690 --> 03:15:38,690
God.

2739
03:15:44,650 --> 03:15:46,610
How can a...

2740
03:15:46,700 --> 03:15:50,280
How can a country come apart like this?

2741
03:15:50,370 --> 03:15:53,370
What have I done wrong?

2742
03:15:55,000 --> 03:15:59,540
I opened China.
I made peace with Russia.

2743
03:16:00,790 --> 03:16:03,880
I ended the war.

2744
03:16:05,550 --> 03:16:08,340
I did what I thought was right.

2745
03:16:13,560 --> 03:16:16,270
God, why do they hate me so?

2746
03:16:16,350 --> 03:16:20,480
It's unbelievable. It... It's insane.

2747
03:16:21,900 --> 03:16:27,320
Oh, Mom, I'm sorry. God, please
forgive me, God. I didn't mean it.

2748
03:16:27,400 --> 03:16:31,070
I never wanted to do...
I don't want this to... Is it me?

2749
03:16:31,160 --> 03:16:34,910
Is this happening?
I can't believe...

2750
03:16:40,750 --> 03:16:42,590
Al.

2751
03:16:58,060 --> 03:17:03,520
They smelled the blood on me
this time, Al. I got soft, you know?

2752
03:17:04,400 --> 03:17:07,860
A rusty, metallic smell.

2753
03:17:07,950 --> 03:17:12,570
- I know it well, sir.
- It came over from Vietnam, you know?

2754
03:17:12,660 --> 03:17:15,200
- Sir?
- That smell.

2755
03:17:16,330 --> 03:17:19,250
I mean, everyone suffered so much.

2756
03:17:19,330 --> 03:17:22,460
Their boys killed.

2757
03:17:22,540 --> 03:17:26,260
They need to sacrifice something.

2758
03:17:26,340 --> 03:17:29,260
You know, appease the gods of war.

2759
03:17:30,130 --> 03:17:33,260
Mars, Jupiter.

2760
03:17:36,350 --> 03:17:39,430
I am that blood, General.

2761
03:17:41,440 --> 03:17:44,230
I am that sacrifice.

2762
03:17:45,020 --> 03:17:47,780
In the highest place of all.

2763
03:17:51,240 --> 03:17:55,410
Yeah. All leaders
must finally be sacrificed.

2764
03:17:56,660 --> 03:17:59,580
Things won't be the same after this.

2765
03:17:59,660 --> 03:18:05,380
No, I played by the rules. Rules changed
right in the middle of the game.

2766
03:18:05,460 --> 03:18:09,170
There's no respect for American
institutions anymore.

2767
03:18:10,920 --> 03:18:13,930
No, people are cynical.

2768
03:18:14,010 --> 03:18:17,680
The press, ah,
the press is out of control.

2769
03:18:19,140 --> 03:18:22,440
People spit on soldiers.

2770
03:18:22,520 --> 03:18:25,060
Government secrets mean nothing.

2771
03:18:26,520 --> 03:18:29,690
I pity the next guy who sits here.

2772
03:18:32,530 --> 03:18:34,700
Good night, gentlemen.

2773
03:18:40,620 --> 03:18:43,170
Mr. President.

2774
03:19:19,660 --> 03:19:24,580
When they look at you,
they see what they want to be.

2775
03:19:27,330 --> 03:19:32,340
When they look at me,
they see what they are.

2776
03:19:37,680 --> 03:19:40,810
Dick, please don't.

2777
03:19:47,350 --> 03:19:49,480
I can't.

2778
03:19:49,560 --> 03:19:52,570
I don't have the strength anymore.

2779
03:19:54,030 --> 03:19:56,200
It'll be over soon.

2780
03:19:56,280 --> 03:19:59,450
No, it's going to start now.

2781
03:20:00,450 --> 03:20:05,500
Oh, Buddy.
If I could just sleep.

2782
03:20:05,580 --> 03:20:08,960
- If I could just sleep.
- There'll be time for that.

2783
03:20:09,040 --> 03:20:10,880
Yeah.

2784
03:20:15,380 --> 03:20:20,220
You know, once when I was sick as a boy,

2785
03:20:20,300 --> 03:20:25,310
my mother gave me this stuff
and she made me swallow it.

2786
03:20:26,730 --> 03:20:29,940
It made me throw up all over her.

2787
03:20:32,070 --> 03:20:35,610
I wish I could do that now.

2788
03:20:41,530 --> 03:20:44,290
I'm so afraid.

2789
03:20:44,950 --> 03:20:47,750
There's darkness out there.

2790
03:20:49,540 --> 03:20:54,840
I could always see where I was going.
But it's dark out there.

2791
03:20:57,170 --> 03:21:01,430
God, I've always
been afraid of the dark.

2792
03:21:03,010 --> 03:21:05,020
Buddy.

2793
03:21:32,040 --> 03:21:32,120
There are many fine careers.
This country needs good farmers,

2794
03:21:32,130 --> 03:21:37,590
There are many fine careers.
This country needs good farmers,

2795
03:21:37,670 --> 03:21:42,640
good businessmen, good plumbers

2796
03:21:42,720 --> 03:21:45,810
good carpenters.

2797
03:21:45,890 --> 03:21:49,390
I remember my old man.

2798
03:21:49,480 --> 03:21:53,060
I think that they would
have called him sort of a,

2799
03:21:53,150 --> 03:21:56,110
sort of a little man, a common man.

2800
03:21:56,190 --> 03:22:01,950
Well, he didn't consider
himself that way.

2801
03:22:02,030 --> 03:22:06,620
You know what he was?
He was a streetcar motorman first.

2802
03:22:06,700 --> 03:22:10,290
Then he was a farmer.

2803
03:22:10,370 --> 03:22:12,330
Then he had a lemon ranch.

2804
03:22:12,420 --> 03:22:16,170
It was the poorest lemon ranch
in California, I can assure you.

2805
03:22:16,250 --> 03:22:19,300
He sold it before they found oil on it.

2806
03:22:22,380 --> 03:22:25,010
Then he was a grocer.

2807
03:22:25,100 --> 03:22:27,600
But he was a great man

2808
03:22:27,680 --> 03:22:30,980
because he did his job.

2809
03:22:31,060 --> 03:22:34,230
And every job counts up to the hilt

2810
03:22:34,310 --> 03:22:36,900
regardless of what happens.

2811
03:22:38,280 --> 03:22:41,780
Nobody will ever write a book,
probably, about my mother.

2812
03:22:41,860 --> 03:22:47,870
Well, I guess all of you would
say this about your mother.

2813
03:22:49,540 --> 03:22:52,910
My mother was a saint.

2814
03:22:53,000 --> 03:22:58,550
And I think of her
two boys dying of tuberculosis

2815
03:22:58,630 --> 03:23:03,430
and seeing each of them die.
And when they died...

2816
03:23:07,890 --> 03:23:13,480
Yes, she will have no books
written about her.

2817
03:23:14,810 --> 03:23:18,400
But she was a saint.

2818
03:23:19,440 --> 03:23:23,400
Now, however, we look to the future.

2819
03:23:23,490 --> 03:23:27,700
I remember something, uh,
Theodore Roosevelt wrote

2820
03:23:27,780 --> 03:23:31,950
when his first wife died
in his twenties.

2821
03:23:32,040 --> 03:23:35,750
He thought the light had gone
from his life forever.

2822
03:23:35,830 --> 03:23:39,420
But he went on, and he not
only became president

2823
03:23:39,500 --> 03:23:42,300
but as an ex-president,
he served his country

2824
03:23:42,380 --> 03:23:46,430
always in the arena,
tempestuous, strong,

2825
03:23:46,510 --> 03:23:49,050
sometimes right, sometimes wrong.

2826
03:23:49,140 --> 03:23:52,310
But he was a man.

2827
03:23:52,390 --> 03:23:58,020
And as I leave that's an example
I think all of us should remember.

2828
03:23:58,100 --> 03:24:03,740
See, we think sometimes when, things
happen that don't go the right way;

2829
03:24:03,820 --> 03:24:07,610
we think that when someone
dear to us dies,

2830
03:24:07,700 --> 03:24:10,530
when we lose an election,

2831
03:24:10,620 --> 03:24:14,290
or when we suffer defeat
that all is ended.

2832
03:24:14,370 --> 03:24:19,330
Not true.
It's only a beginning, always,

2833
03:24:19,420 --> 03:24:23,630
because the greatness comes,
not when things go always good for you,

2834
03:24:23,710 --> 03:24:27,680
but the greatness comes
when you're really tested,

2835
03:24:27,760 --> 03:24:31,470
when you take some knocks,
some disappointments

2836
03:24:31,550 --> 03:24:33,640
when sadness comes.

2837
03:24:33,720 --> 03:24:37,810
Because only if you've been
in the deepest valley

2838
03:24:37,890 --> 03:24:43,480
can you ever know
how magnificent it is

2839
03:24:43,570 --> 03:24:45,820
to be on the highest mountain.

2840
03:24:49,410 --> 03:24:52,700
So, I say to you on this occasion,

2841
03:24:52,780 --> 03:24:57,160
we leave, proud of the people
who have stood by us and worked for us

2842
03:24:57,250 --> 03:25:00,710
and served this government
and this country.

2843
03:25:00,790 --> 03:25:03,590
They want you to continue
to serve in government

2844
03:25:03,670 --> 03:25:05,800
if that is what you wish.

2845
03:25:05,880 --> 03:25:09,380
Remember, always give your best.

2846
03:25:09,470 --> 03:25:13,720
Never get discouraged.
Never be petty.

2847
03:25:13,810 --> 03:25:17,390
Always remember, others may hate you.

2848
03:25:17,480 --> 03:25:21,730
But those who hate you don't win
unless you hate them.

2849
03:25:21,810 --> 03:25:26,480
And then, you destroy yourself.

2850
03:25:26,570 --> 03:25:32,280
And so we leave with high hopes
and good spirits and with deep humility.

2851
03:25:32,370 --> 03:25:34,490
And I say to each
and every one of you,

2852
03:25:34,580 --> 03:25:36,950
not only will we always remember you

2853
03:25:37,040 --> 03:25:42,290
but always, you will be
in our hearts.

2854
03:25:42,380 --> 03:25:46,960
And you'll be in our prayers.

2855
03:25:47,050 --> 03:25:53,050
And only then will you find what
we Quakers call "peace at the center".

2856
03:26:07,820 --> 03:26:13,780
He gave of himself with intelligence
and energy and devotion to duty.

2857
03:26:13,870 --> 03:26:19,700
<i>Richard Nixon was buried and honored
by five presidents on April 26, 1994.</i>

2858
03:26:19,790 --> 03:26:24,580
<i>Less than a year after his beloved wife,
Pat, had died.</i>

2859
03:26:24,670 --> 03:26:28,460
<i>Nixon always maintained that
if he had not been driven from office</i>

2860
03:26:28,550 --> 03:26:33,800
<i>the North Vietnamese would not have
overwhelmed the South in 1975.</i>

2861
03:26:33,890 --> 03:26:38,560
<i>In a sideshow, Cambodian society was
destroyed and mass genocide resulted.</i>

2862
03:26:38,640 --> 03:26:43,270
The second half of the 20th century
will be known as the age of Nixon.

2863
03:26:43,350 --> 03:26:46,860
<i>ln his absence, Russia and the
United States returned to a decade</i>

2864
03:26:46,940 --> 03:26:49,610
<i>of high-budget military expansion
and near war.</i>

2865
03:26:50,530 --> 03:26:53,570
<i>Nixon, who was pardoned
by President Ford,</i>

2866
03:26:53,660 --> 03:26:59,240
<i>lived to write six books and travel
the world as an elder statesman.</i>

2867
03:26:59,330 --> 03:27:04,370
<i>For the remainder of his life, he fought
successfully to protect his tapes.</i>

2868
03:27:04,460 --> 03:27:09,250
<i>The National Archives spent
14 years indexing and cataloging them.</i>

2869
03:27:09,340 --> 03:27:13,800
<i>Out of 4,000 hours,
60 hours have been made public.</i>

2870
03:30:15,800 --> 03:30:15,800
ESiR

